[img]http://static.metal-archives.com/images/5/8/1/4/58143_photo.jpg[/img]

He signed his first record deal in 1993 with a band called Strip Mind. Their debut album "What's in Your Mouth" sold less than 50,000 units. The band self-destructed shortly after. They toured throughout the US several times. 
Stu Shoaps - Vocals / Guitar (Seka)
Tim Catz - Bass / Backing Vocals (Seka)
Billy O'Malley - Guitar / Vocals (Seka)
Sully Erna - Drums (ex-Meliah Rage, Godsmack)

I'd personally classify this as a Metal/Rock/Thrash and a touch of punk.  Sully is on drums, as he has always been a drummer, up until Godsmack started to tour when he did vocals.
